.TH "work_on_cpu" 9 "work_on_cpu" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
work_on_cpu \- run a function in thread context on a particular cpu
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "long" work_on_cpu
.BI "(int cpu "  ","
.BI "long (*fn)(void *) "  ","
.BI "void *arg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cpu" 12
the cpu to run on
.IP "fn" 12
the function to run
.IP "arg" 12
the function arg
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It is up to the caller to ensure that the cpu doesn't go offline.
The caller must not hold any locks which would prevent \fIfn\fP from completing.
.SH "RETURN"
The value \fIfn\fP returns.
